Description:
We are the Global IT Solution Centre for Roche - one of the largest and most innovative pharmaceutical companies in the world.
We do #Code4life creating innovative software that helps doctors, patients, and scientists around the world.
We are looking for experienced, self-driven R developers who want to join an agile international team of scientists and software engineers that work on a new R-based toolchain to transform how we process and analyze data in clinical trials.
We expect from the candidate:
Proficiency in R programming including documented experience with package development according to best practices;
Experience with R packages commonly used for data munging and visualization;
Advanced R Shiny skills, including writing Shiny modules, testing Shiny applications, scalability, and deployment;
Experience with modern R frameworks such as the tidyverse, data.table, or similar;
Knowledge of Python is a plus;
Knowledge of data visualization tools and/or use of REST API with containers using Plumber;
Experience with code repositories is a must, including w orking with GitHub/Gitlab or even Bitbucket, creating branches, familiarity with git workflows;
Nice to have knowledge with CI/CD automation ( i.e Travis CI, Github actions, Gitlab CI/CD, Jenkins, Bamboo);
Familiarity/Experience with R package representations & structure;
Experience developing/contributing to mature R packages that exercise many software development best practices;
Added advantages:
Package testing , using testthat or some other testing utility ;(i.eRUnit);
Experience with code coverage utils would be nice;
Metaprogramming skills as an added advantage to understand the intricacies of the language;
Experience dealing with package repositories outside of CRAN and Bioconductor, such as a company-wide package repository;
Your job will require:
Working in an agile environment in a multidisciplinary team;
Ability to directly communicate with research scientists and understand business requirements for scientific applications
Work on open source projects;
To have a growth mindset with an attitude to continuously learning new technologies and exploring new business areas;
We offer:
Permanent full-time employment with a truly global company
Attractive benefits & relocation package
Opportunities for personal and professional self-development (training, certifications, conferences, diversified career paths etc.)
Experienced, professional colleagues and workplace that supports innovation and new ideas
A chance to work on solutions which can improve patients’ live
